summary: This is an email from the U.S. Customs and Border Protection (CBP) system to the FBI, notifying them of a 'query hit' on Ghislaine Maxwell's lookout record. It indicates that her record was accessed via a Person Lookout Query from the CBP's National Targeting Center in Reston, VA.

events.title: CBP Query Hit on Ghislaine Maxwell
events.description: The U.S. Customs and Border Protection (CBP) system generated a notification that Ghislaine Maxwell's record (TECSID: P3O92965500A01) was accessed via a Person Lookout Query from the CBP's National Targeting Center in Reston.

locations: CBP-RESTON, NAIL TARGETING CTR (Reston, VA, USA)
keyFacts: On March 9, 2021, U.S. Customs and Border Protection (CBP) sent an automated notification to the FBI regarding a query hit on Ghislaine Maxwell.
The query was a 'Person Lookout Query' conducted from the CBP's National Targeting Center in Reston, VA.
Maxwell's record in the system had a specific identifier: TECSID: P3O92965500A01.
The email indicates ongoing law enforcement monitoring or interest in Maxwell's travel or status in early 2021.
